===Etymology===

Name Afghan is believed to have derived from [[Sanskrit]] ''Ashvakan'' meaning horseman. Suffix ''stan'' has the meaning ''land'' in [[Persian]], thereby,  ''Afghan + stan'' = Afghanistan,  which means the land of Afghans. See: ''List of country name etymologies'' at [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_country_name_etymologies].

===Pronunciation===
*Af'ga'nis'tan

===Proper noun===
'''Afghanistan'''
#a country in Central Asia. Official name: Afghanistan. Capital: Kabul. Official languages: [[Persian]] ([[Dari]]), [[Pashto]].
